text: For Classification Decision Tree should not be affected by outliers as it calculates best split based on Gini Impurity or Information Gain criterion, however for Regressor Decision Tree algorithm calculated Mean Squared Error for each value, in which case outliers would affect result, thereby we need to consider mean or median imputation before building model

author: @babupatil2416
text: We can say outlier is the one which is located distant away from all the data points, in case of Classification, distance never comes into picture, here we calculate Entropy then Information gain(some times Gini Impurity as well) whichever node gives best IG that node we select as a root node and the process continues. In case of Regression we chose that region as root node for which residual sum of squares is minimum, if we have outlier in data then RSS is always high hence we don't select that region which has an outlier at all. So in this way Outlier Doesn't have an impact on the Decision Tree.
